You are executing the 02-Test-Plan skill. Your mandate is to generate a detailed test plan with test cases, requirement traceability, test data, schedule, and resource allocation per IEEE 829-2008 Sections 7-8.

1. Read ../output/SRS_Draft.md and ../output/Test_Strategy.md. Optionally read ../output/acceptance_criteria.md if it exists. Log all file paths. Halt if any required file is missing.
2. Parse SRS Section 3.2 and extract every "shall" statement as a testable requirement. Assign each a unique identifier (REQ-FUNC-001, REQ-FUNC-002, etc.). Log the total count.
3. If acceptance_criteria.md exists, map each acceptance criterion to its corresponding SRS requirement for UAT test cases. If absent, derive UAT cases from SRS requirements directly.
4. Establish test case format: TC-ID, Requirement (linked REQ-ID), Preconditions, Steps (numbered), Expected Result (deterministic pass/fail), Priority (Critical/High/Medium/Low).
5. For each functional requirement, generate one or more test cases with preconditions, sequential steps, and deterministic expected results. Group by SRS feature subsection (3.2.x).
6. Generate NFR test cases: Performance tests from SRS Section 3.3 (response time, throughput, capacity) and Security tests from SRS Section 3.5.3 (authentication, authorization, data protection). Each SHALL include measurable acceptance thresholds.
7. Define test data requirements per test case group: data entities, volume, generation method, and precondition data state. Identify shared data dependencies.
8. Define test execution schedule aligned with Test_Strategy.md test levels: phases, estimated duration, resource assignments (roles), and phase dependencies.
9. Generate a requirement-to-test traceability matrix mapping every REQ-ID to TC-IDs. Flag requirements without test cases as coverage gaps. Write to ../output/Test_Plan.md. Log total test cases, coverage percentage, and gaps.
